2. ✅POAHelper.narrow(...)
- The returned object is generic (Object)
- narrow() converts it into a POA type, narrow method is used for type-safe casting of generic object references.

“Type-safe casting” means converting an object from one type to another in a way that guarantees at runtime 
that the conversion is valid, preventing unexpected errors.

Similar to:
(TypeCasting)

Without narrowing, you can't use POA methods

A generic object simply means an object that is referred to using a very general type, rather than a specific 
one.

In Java terms
=============
The most common “generic object” is:

Object obj;
Object is the parent (superclass) of all classes in Java
So obj can point to any kind of object

Example:

Object obj;

obj = "Hello";     // String object
obj = 42;          // Integer object (autoboxed)
obj = new Date();  // Date object

Here, obj is a generic reference because it doesn’t specify what kind of object it holds.

List of POA methods in CORBA?
=============================
In CORBA, the Portable Object Adapter (POA) provides methods to manage object lifecycles, servants, and request processing.

Here’s a clear list of the commonly used POA methods, grouped by purpose:

1. POA Creation & Management
	These methods deal with creating and managing POAs:
		create_POA(String adapter_name, POAManager manager, Policy[] policies)
		find_POA(String adapter_name, boolean activate_it)
		destroy(boolean etherealize_objects, boolean wait_for_completion)

2. POA Manager Access
		✅the_POAManager()

	Returns the POA manager that controls request processing (activate, hold, discard, etc.)

3. Object Activation & Deactivation
	Used to associate servants with CORBA objects:
		activate_object(Servant servant)
		activate_object_with_id(byte[] id, Servant servant)
		deactivate_object(byte[] id)

4. Reference Creation
	Convert servants into CORBA object references:
		✅servant_to_reference(Servant servant)
		servant_to_id(Servant servant)
		id_to_reference(byte[] id)
		id_to_servant(byte[] id)
		reference_to_servant(org.omg.CORBA.Object reference)
		reference_to_id(org.omg.CORBA.Object reference)

5. ID & Servant Mapping
	Helps map between IDs, servants, and references:
		create_reference(String repository_id)
		create_reference_with_id(byte[] oid, String repository_id)

6. Policy Access
		get_servant_manager()
		set_servant_manager(ServantManager manager)
		get_servant()
		set_servant(Servant servant)

7. POA Hierarchy & Info
		the_name()
		the_parent()
		the_children()
		the_activator()
		the_activator(AdapterActivator activator)

8. Request Processing Control
		Indirectly controlled via POAManager, but relevant:
		(via POAManager) ✅activate(), hold_requests(), discard_requests(), deactivate()

Key Idea
		The POA is responsible for:
		Creating object references
		Connecting them to servants
		Managing object lifecycle
		Controlling how requests are handled

